Certificate of Currency
Date of Issue: 30 June 2022
Main Roads Western Australia PO Box 6202 EAST PERTH WA 6892
Contact: Leonie Tate Client Director Aon Risk Solutions Level 15, 28 The Esplanade Perth WA 6000, Australia t: +61 8 6317 4044 e: leonie.tate@aon.com
We hereby certify that the under mentioned insurance policy is current as at the date of this certificate, please refer to the important notices below.
Policy Type
Maintenance Liability Floater
Insured
The Commissioner of Main Roads Western Australia (as Principals and/or Contractors). Other parties as specified in the definition of Insured
Named Insured Representatives
Manager Legal and Commercial Services Main Roads – Western Australia Don Aitken Centre, Waterloo Crescent, East Perth, Western Australia 6004
Insurer(s)
Certain Underwriters at Lloyd’s of London / Berkshire Hathaway Specialty Insurance (Australia) / Swiss Re International SE (Australia)
Lead Policy Number(s)
CSINT2202773 / CSINT2200903 / CSINT2200915
Period of Insurance
From: 4.00 pm 30 June 2022 Local Standard Time To: 4.00 pm 30 June 2023 Local Standard Time
Defects Liability Period
48 months any one Contract
Interest Insured
Losses occurring during the Period of Insurance Basis
All Contracts of any kind or description undertaken during the Period of Insurance or which are on hand at the commencement of the Period of Insurance, by or on behalf of the Named Insured, where the estimated contract value is less than $100,000,000.
Limit(s) of Liability
$250,000,000 any one Occurrence $250,000,000 in the separate aggregate annually from inception for all Occurrences in respect of Pollution, Products / Defects Liability.
Geographical Limit(s)
Anywhere in the world but excluding any operations of the Insured domiciled in the United States of America or Canada. Notwithstanding the above, indemnity is provided to the Insured in respect of: 1) Products exported into those countries; and to 2) Directors of the Insured or Employees who are non-resident in such countries; and 3) Any person or firm engaged in a consultative capacity in such countries
Further Information
Should you have any queries, please contact us on the details set out at the top of the page.
Important notes
• Aon does not guarantee that the insurance outlined in this Certificate will continue to remain in force for the period referred to as the Policy may be cancelled or altered by either party to the contract, at any time, in accordance with the terms of the Policy and the Insurance Contracts Act 1984 (Clth).
• Aon accepts no responsibility or liability to advise any party who may be relying on this Certificate of such alteration to or cancellation of the Policy. • Subject to full payment of premium
• This certificate does not:
- represent an insurance contract or confer rights to the recipient;
- amend, extend or alter the Policy; or
- contain the full policy terms and conditions
Aon Reference: AONPER0XBDN
